name: hypertunes
description: An open source music player app, with support for custom backends, made with Electron.

releases.name: Lyrics!
releases.body: Adds lyrics input, synching, and display (the user has to acquire and sync the lyrics themselves, for legal reasons).

releases.name: Easy Plugin Management
releases.body: This release adds easy plugin management through the settings, allowing for installing and removing plugins. On a minor note, the settings have been refactored, and a `fetchImage` property function has been added to `PlayerBackend`s which is called to try and get an image for metadata without images.

releases.name: More playlist control
releases.body: This release adds more playlist control (deletion, renaming, removing songs from them). That's it.

releases.name: Support for pluginable backends!
releases.body:
This release adds support for pluginable backends! This enables plugins for different player backends to be created, allowing music to be played from, say, Spotify, YouTube, and more (given, of course, that plugins for them were made). This release also contains some bug fixes (can't remember them all ð ), among them a fix for the player skipping over songs automatically.

TODO:
- Document plugin interface
- Simplify plugin installation

releases.name: Playlist support, Material icons (for the sidebar)
releases.body: This release adds playlist support (finally!) and Material icons (for 2 sidebar icons), plus a custom "about" popup. The point-one patch is because I forgot to update the playlist page in v1.8.0 (oops, ð ).

releases.name: Revert v1.7.3
releases.body: Version 1.7.3 introduced a playback bug, which I honestly don't have time to look into (plus I have other, more important features to develop), so this just reverts back to version 1.7.2. All v1.7.3 did was make a style fix (features are more important, and I can do it again later, probably with a more stable method, like icon fonts).

releases.name: Another bug fix
releases.body: Fixes the bug where requesting a rescan would immediately reload the library instead of waiting.

releases.name: Bug fixes
releases.body:
Fixes 2 bugs:
- Settings/theme not loaded on startup
- Album songs are not listed in order (by track number)

releases.name: MInor overhaul
releases.body:
It's not that much of an overhaul, but a lot of the audio logic was rewritten, so...
- Code rewrite
- Custom theme colors
- Initial playlist support

releases.name: Last.fm Scrobbling
releases.body:
Scrobbling support for Last.fm, you can sign in through the settings.

(on a minor note, updated to Electron v1.1.1, which doesn't have the Windows VCRuntime bug anymore, I think)

releases.name: Settings Support
releases.body: This release adds support for settings, well... _a_ setting. It currently has only 1 setting, the path to the music folder.

releases.name: Extra Windows Support
releases.body: Specifically, it supports Squirrel installer commands (not auto-updating, though) and Windows 7 tray balloon notifications.

releases.name: v1.4.0
releases.body: I forgot to install the new dependencies in v1.3.0, oops ð

releases.name: v1.3.0
releases.body:
Various improvements and bug fixes:
- No more native dependencies (fixes issues with cross-platform binaries)
- Fixed Windows library path issue
- Style fixes
- Shows a message if no songs were found

releases.name: v1.2.0
releases.body: Chromecast support! Also, improved cross-platform support.

releases.name: Initial Release
releases.body:
Basic music player functionality, plus:
- autoplaying the next song in an album
- album covers
- media keys support

More coming soon...
